name: Lacey Family Medicine - Covid Vaccine Site
notes:
THIS IS A PFIZER DOSE 1 and 2 CLINIC 

Before you schedule your appointment there are some important things that you need to know about your vaccination:

Please arrive as close as possible to your scheduled time to prevent crowding that will impede appropriate social distancing.
Please wear clothes that will allow for access to your upper arm, just below the shoulder.
All minors with appointments must be accompanied by a parent or guardian or sent with written consent.
Please do not bring children who are not receiving a vaccine to your appointment, they will not be allowed into the clinic.
If needed, only one support person, per patient, will be admitted.
If you are signing up for a second dose, you must get the same vaccine brand as your first dose.

name: Olympic Pharmacy and Healthcare Services - COVID Vaccine Venue
notes:
**This clinic is for the JANSSEN/ JOHNSON & JOHNSON COVID -19 vaccine.  It is a Single Dose vaccination**

Vaccine in indicated for Adults 18 years of age and older.

Please bring your State ID, and if you have insurance, please bring your insurance card or Medicare B card (red,white and blue card).

Please do not come to the clinic if you are not feeling well.

Please wear loose sleeved, short sleeved or sleeveless shirt.

When you enter Olympic Pharmacy, please follow COVID clinic signs to the back conference/fitting area. This clinic is not in the pharmacy area.

Please arrive as close as possible to your scheduled time to prevent crowding that will impede appropriate social distancing

Please be prepared to wait 15-30 minutes after vaccination for observation of adverse reactions.

If appointments are full, you can click on “Waiting List” to register yourself for standby appointments. If there are extra doses of vaccine at the end of the day, individuals on the waiting list will be called in scheduling order.
If you are signing up for a second dose, you must get the same vaccine brand as your first dose.

name: Rebel Med NW - COVID Vaccine Clinic
notes:
***We will accept both first and second dose appointments*** ***Please notify us of a cancelation ASAP, we have patients on waiting list, and would prefer not to waste vaccines*** You must provide insurance (photo ID if you do not have insurance) by one of the 2 methods below before you check-in for vaccine. Upload options 1. Prepmod at time of sign up 2. bring your insurance card to your visit.

We are administering the first/second dose of the Moderna vaccine. Moderna is currently approved for all adults 18 years and older. Please bring a face covering that covers the mouth and nose. Everyone is required to stay 15-30 minutes under observation after receiving the vaccine.

Rebel Med NW is located on the 2nd floor, with the entrance on NW Vernon Place. Across the street from the Olympic Athletic Club. We are an integrative medical clinic specializing in Naturopathic Primary Care, Acupuncture, and Mind Body Medicine. Please be respectful of the space as treatments may be ongoing. Please contact 206-297-6013, and ask to speak to a provider on call if you have a question, leave a voicemail and we will return as soon as we are available.

Call 911 if life-threatening emergency, and you are in need of immediate help.
If you are signing up for a second dose, you must get the same vaccine brand as your first dose.
